<main>
    <h1 id='header'>Best Beautiful Brisket</h1>
    <img src='../images/brisket.jpeg' alt='a beautiful brisket' style='width:400;height:600;'>

    <div>
        <h4>Ingredients</h4>
        <ul>
            <li>Brisket</li>
            <li>Smoker (I use electric with mix of cherry and oak chips)</li>
            <li>Chef's Knife</li>
            <li>Cutting Board</li>
            <li>Peach Butcher Paper</li>
            <li>Meat Thermometer</li>
          
        </ul>
    </div>
    <div>
        <h4>Recipe</h4>
        <ol>
            <li>Select your brikset</li>
            <li>Trim up your brisket</li>
            <li>Season your brisket.  I lather my mustard before adding seasonign (optional).  Texas style indicates only salt and pepper but I like to use some garlic powder, and brpwn sugar.</li>
            <li>Wrap your brisket with the butcher paper</li>
            <li>Smoke your brisket until it reaches an internal temperature of 202F.</li>
            <li>Rest your brisket</li>
            <li>Slice your brisket</li>
            <li>Enjoy and mentally thank me</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
